"Implement the following plan:\n\n# Fix Droid \"(no prompt)\" after commit\n\n## Context\n\nWhen a Factory AI Droid session creates checkpoints and the user commits, `entire explain` shows `(no prompt)` for the committed checkpoint. Before the commit, the temporary (shadow branch) checkpoint correctly shows the prompt.\n\n**Root cause**: Three functions parse transcripts in an agent-aware way (Gemini vs Claude Code) but lack a Droid-specific path. Since Droid uses a different JSONL envelope (`{\"type\":\"message\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"user\",...}}`) vs Claude Code (`{\"type\":\"user\",\"message\":{\"content\":...}}`), the generic Claude Code parser fails to find user messages. The top-level `type` is always `\"message\"`, which doesn't match the `\"user\"`/`\"human\"` check.\n\nTemporary checkpoints work because `SaveStep()` uses the agent-specific `ExtractPrompts()` method (in `lifecycle.go`) which correctly handles the Droid envelope. Committed checkpoints fail because condensation re-extracts prompts from the raw transcript using the generic parser.\n\n## Changes\n\n### 1. Add Droid handling to `extractUserPrompts()`\n**File**: `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_condensation.go:500-527`\n\nAdd a `case agent.AgentTypeFactoryAIDroid` branch that uses `factoryaidroid.ParseDroidTranscriptFromBytes()` to normalize the transcript, then extracts user messages from the normalized lines using `transcript.ExtractUserContent()`.\n\n```go\nfunc extractUserPrompts(agentType agent.AgentType, content string) []string {\n    if content == \"\" {\n        return nil\n    }\n\n    // Droid has its own envelope format — use its parser\n    if agentType == agent.AgentTypeFactoryAIDroid {\n        lines, err := factoryaidroid.ParseDroidTranscriptFromBytes([]byte(content))\n        if err != nil {\n            return nil\n        }\n        var prompts []string\n        for _, line := range lines {\n            if line.Type != transcript.TypeUser {\n                continue\n            }\n            if text := transcript.ExtractUserContent(line.Message); text != \"\" {\n                if stripped := textutil.StripIDEContextTags(text); stripped != \"\" {\n                    prompts = append(prompts, stripped)\n                }\n            }\n        }\n        return prompts\n    }\n\n    // (existing Gemini + Claude Code logic unchanged)\n    ...\n}\n```\n\n### 2. Add Droid handling to `calculateTokenUsage()`\n**File**: `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_condensation.go:533-562`\n\nAdd a `case agent.AgentTypeFactoryAIDroid` branch that uses `factoryaidroid.ParseDroidTranscriptFromBytes()` + `factoryaidroid.CalculateTokenUsage()`.\n\n```go\nfunc calculateTokenUsage(agentType agent.AgentType, data []byte, startOffset int) *agent.TokenUsage {\n    ...\n    // Droid has its own envelope format — use its parser\n    if agentType == agent.AgentTypeFactoryAIDroid {\n        lines, err := factoryaidroid.ParseDroidTranscriptFromBytes(data)\n        if err != nil || len(lines) == 0 {\n            return &agent.TokenUsage{}\n        }\n        if startOffset > 0 && startOffset < len(lines) {\n            lines = lines[startOffset:]\n        }\n        return factoryaidroid.CalculateTokenUsage(lines)\n    }\n    ...\n}\n```\n\n### 3. Add Droid handling to `BuildCondensedTranscriptFromBytes()`\n**File**: `cmd/entire/cli/summarize/summarize.go:115-128`\n\nThe function already groups `AgentTypeFactoryAIDroid` with Claude Code (line 119), but then uses `transcript.ParseFromBytes()` which doesn't normalize the Droid envelope. Fix: use `factoryaidroid.ParseDroidTranscriptFromBytes()` for Droid, then pass normalized lines to `BuildCondensedTranscript()`.\n\n```go\nfunc BuildCondensedTranscriptFromBytes(content []byte, agentType agent.AgentType) ([]Entry, error) {\n    switch agentType {\n    case agent.AgentTypeGemini:\n        return buildCondensedTranscriptFromGemini(content)\n    case agent.AgentTypeFactoryAIDroid:\n        lines, err := factoryaidroid.ParseDroidTranscriptFromBytes(content)\n        if err != nil {\n            return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"failed to parse Droid transcript: %w\", err)\n        }\n        return BuildCondensedTranscript(lines), nil\n    case agent.AgentTypeClaudeCode, agent.AgentTypeUnknown:\n        // Claude format - fall through to shared logic below\n    }\n    lines, err := transcript.ParseFromBytes(content)\n    if err != nil {\n        return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"failed to parse transcript: %w\", err)\n    }\n    return BuildCondensedTranscript(lines), nil\n}\n```\n\n### 4. Add import for `factoryaidroid` package\n**Files**:\n- `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_condensation.go` - add `\"github.com/entireio/cli/cmd/entire/cli/agent/factoryaidroid\"`\n- `cmd/entire/cli/summarize/summarize.go` - add `\"github.com/entireio/cli/cmd/entire/cli/agent/factoryaidroid\"`\n\nBoth files already import other agent packages (`claudecode`, `geminicli`), so this is consistent.\n\n## Existing code to reuse\n\n- `factoryaidroid.ParseDroidTranscriptFromBytes()` — `cmd/entire/cli/agent/factoryaidroid/transcript.go:50` — normalizes Droid JSONL to `transcript.Line` (already exists, tested)\n- `factoryaidroid.CalculateTokenUsage()` — `cmd/entire/cli/agent/factoryaidroid/transcript.go:171` — computes token usage from normalized lines (already exists, handles streaming dedup)\n- `transcript.ExtractUserContent()` — `cmd/entire/cli/transcript/parse.go` — extracts text from normalized message (already used by Droid's `ExtractPrompts()`)\n- `textutil.StripIDEContextTags()` — strips IDE context tags (already used everywhere)\n\n## Verification\n\n1. `mise run fmt && mise run lint && mise run test:ci` — all tests pass, no lint errors\n2. Manual test: run a Droid session, create a checkpoint, commit, then `entire explain` — prompt should now appear\n3. Existing integration tests should continue to pass (no behavioral change for Claude Code or Gemini)\n\n\nIf you need specific details from before exit